cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SC 

This paper is primarily focused on the theoretical properties of convolutional neural networks, specifically those with rectified linear activation and max or average pooling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also uses mathematical tools from the world of arithmetic circuits, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
